node_modules/
# dist/ is committed to the repo so git-URL consumers (e.g.
# `bun add git+https://github.com/...#<sha>`) get a working build WITHOUT
# needing to run the `prepare` hook. Bun's default-off trusted-script
# policy and devDependency resolution quirks make prepare unreliable for
# some install flows; committing dist/ sidesteps both. Trade-off:
# +≈500 KB git size and dist/ diffs accompanying src/ edits. See
# khal-os/brain PR #353 CI failure that triggered this switch.
*.js.map
*.d.ts.map
.env
.env.*

# Scaffolded config files (user-generated, not part of the package)
/SYSTEM.md
/CONTEXT.md
/TOOLS.md
/CRITERIA.md
/MODEL.md
python/__pycache__/
competition/
